# Testing philosophy (Orbit Wars)

Adapted from [cursorrules-collection `practices/testing.mdc`](https://github.com/nedcodes-ok/cursorrules-collection/blob/main/rules-mdc/practices/testing.mdc). Pytest mechanics live in `pytest.mdc`.

## What to assert

- Behavior from the caller’s view: golden `encode_turn` shapes in `tests/test_feature_encoding_golden.py`, not private helper call order.
- Edge cases: empty pools, zero `pool_size` with curriculum on, invalid Hydra overrides, boundary update counts.
- Error paths: `ValueError` from config composition, gate failures — not only happy-path rollouts.

## Mocking

- Mock at boundaries: filesystem checkpoints, subprocess Docker/tournament, external HTTP — not internals of PPO or `encode_turn`.
- Prefer real small fixtures over heavy mocks for game logic in `src/game/`.
- Fixed seeds for RNG/JAX where flakiness appeared; document seed in the test name or fixture.

## Tiers (mandatory)

- Default: `make test` / `make test-fast` — `-m "not slow and not jax and not sweep"`.
- JAX compile: `make test-jax` or domain jax tests — not during every edit.
- **Never** bare `pytest -n` / `-n auto`; use `make test-fast-parallel` only when documented; `tests/conftest.py` blocks undisciplined xdist.
- Check terminals folder before pytest if another session may be running tests.

## Flaky tests

- Fix or delete; no indefinite `xfail` for race/GPU contention.
- No `sleep()` for training completion — poll metrics files or use test doubles.
